OL,3,C'It was overwhelming': rugby player on
OL,4,Cmental health impact of racist abuse
OL,6,F"I never thought I would receive some
OL,7,Fof the abuse that I did as frequently
OL,8,Fas I did. Every time I'd tweet.
OL,10,F"I've always experienced racism at
OL,11,Fsome point in my life in different
OL,12,Fforms, different ways. But the stuff
OL,13,Fthat I was getting on Twitter was just
OL,14,Fcompletely overwhelming."
OL,16,FTo his eternal credit, the winger -
OL,17,Fwho is a grandson of the Windrush
OL,18,Fgeneration - chose to engage and he
OL,19,Fsuffered further.
