OL,3,C'It was overwhelming': rugby player on
OL,4,Cmental health impact of racist abuse
OL,6,FHe explains: "It was probably one of
OL,7,Fthe most difficult things to deal with
OL,8,Ffor me. A lot of times my mum would be
OL,9,Fcrying, seeing the stuff that was
OL,10,Fbeing said to me. My younger sister
OL,11,Fcouldn't understand why I was putting
OL,12,Fmyself in the position that I was - to
OL,13,Ftake all of that abuse.
OL,15,F"(It brought back) incidents of racism
OL,16,Fas a kid that I'd forgotten about. My
OL,17,Fmum would reflect on them, questioning
OL,18,Fif she'd dealt with things and done
OL,19,Fenough herself to sort of protect me
OL,20,For make a difference in whatever
OL,21,Fenvironment it was."
